### C2. Error Retry Button

> [!NOTE]
> When a command fails, the user currently has to retype it. Adding a retry button on error cards is a small but impactful UX win.

#### [MODIFY] [EventCard.js](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/components/EventCard.js)

- For `error` type events, add a "Retry" button below the error message
- On click, dispatch the original command text through the command input

#### [MODIFY] [EventTimeline.js](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/components/EventTimeline.js)

- Pass `onRetry(commandText)` callback through to EventCard
- On retry, call `onCommandSubmit(commandText)` from MainScreen

#### [MODIFY] [components.css](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/styles/components.css)

- Style `.event-card__retry-btn` — small pill button with blue accent

**Effort**: ~30 min

---

### C3. Multi-Step Workflow Stepper

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Compound commands like "find resume and send to X" go through multiple stages (search → disambiguate → ask recipient → confirm → send). Currently the user sees each stage as separate chat bubbles. This consolidates them into a single stepper card.

#### [NEW] [WorkflowStepper.js](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/components/WorkflowStepper.js)

- New component that groups sequential events from a single job into a vertical stepper
- Each step shows: icon → label → status (pending/active/done/failed)
- Connector lines between steps with animated fill

#### [MODIFY] [EventTimeline.js](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/components/EventTimeline.js)

- Detect multi-step jobs (>2 non-ack events before result)
- Render `WorkflowStepper` instead of individual event cards for those jobs

#### [MODIFY] [components.css](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/styles/components.css)

- Stepper styles: `.workflow-stepper`, `.workflow-step`, `.workflow-step__connector`

**Effort**: ~1.5 hours

---

