## Phase D — Stretch Features (4–6 hours)

### D1. Push Notifications (Desktop → Mobile)

> [!WARNING]
> Requires HTTPS for the Push API to work on mobile browsers. During local dev, only works in Chrome on `localhost`.

#### [NEW] [notifications.js](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/mobileapp/src/services/notifications.js)

- Request notification permission on app start
- Subscribe to a periodic poll endpoint `GET /notifications` (or piggyback on health check)
- Show browser notifications for proactive events (battery low, unread emails, etc.)

#### [MODIFY] [server.py](file:///c:/Users/jithi/Documents/ARC_REMOTE/ARC-REMOTE-DA/remote/server.py)

- Add `GET /notifications` endpoint that returns pending proactive alerts
- Add `POST /notifications/dismiss` to mark alerts as seen

#### [NEW] Proactive alert sources in Python backend:
- Battery check (periodic, alert at <15%)
- Email count (when read_emails returns unread count)

**Effort**: ~2 hours

